table_caption: Cognitive Test Scores for PD-MCI and PD-NC Groups.
table_foot: Note. Block design, VF letters, D-KEFS VF categories, D-KEFS. TMT numbers, TMT switching, TMT motor, TMT scanning, and spatial span are scaled scores (M = 10, SD = 3). CVLT (single trial) and SDMT are Z-scores (M = 0, SD = 1). CVLT (total) is a T-score (M = 50, SD = 10).Abbreviations: CVLT, the California Verbal Learning Test; SDMT, the Symbol Digit Modalities Test; TMT, Trail Making Test; VF, Verbal Fluency.*p <.05.
